title: Marrakech Henna Art Cafe
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, International, Middle Eastern, Moroccan, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Cafe and art gallery. Offers traditional Moroccan food with some veggie dishes plus daily specials with international emphasis. Veg include aubergine caviar (eggplant cooked in tomatoes), Latifa's salad (raw cabbage, carrot, and apples in mayonnaise dressing), Moroccan salad, chickpea pate (hummus), lentils with rice, courgette salad, falafel sandwich with taktouka, couscous with vegetables, seasonal fruit with yogurt and granola (dairy), and others. Hot and cold drinks include fresh squeezed orange juice and fruit smoothies. Short walk from Djemaa el Fna Square, look for its blue door painted with henna designs. Free Wi-Fi.
